	     Mahikeng – A North West teacher who went missing over the weekend was found dead, police said on Thursday. Thulisile Ngwenya, 56, was found dead in the bushes near Bokone village, in the North West on Wednesday. ALSO READ: Primary school teacher shot dead in front of her pupils Police spokesperson Captain Yvonne Maqoboza said her decomposed body was found by a shepherd. Ngwenya was a teacher at Lekoko Primary School outside Mahikeng. She was last seen on Saturday morning and reported missing on Sunday. ALSO READ: KZN teacher's body found in storm water drain after flash floods Maqoboza said her vehicle, a Mazda CX3, was found parked near Mahikeng taxi rank. Police are investigating murder and kidnapping.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  